dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Chandrayaan-1_Parameters
class.description: Container class for general Chandrayaan-1 related parameters.

class.title: Initial_Spacecraft_Orientation
class.description: Class for the initial Chandrayaan-1 spacecraft orientation parameters, roll/pitch/yaw in degrees from 'ideal nadir'

class.title: Spacecraft_Orientation
class.description: Class for Chandrayaan-1 spacecraft orientation parameters, roll/pitch/yaw in degrees from 'ideal nadir'

class.title: Spacecraft_Orientation_Axis_Vector
class.description: Class for Chandrayaan-1 spacecraft orientation axis vector, x/y/z unit vector wrt J2000 describing rotation direction since epoch

class.title: Spacecraft_Orientation_Rates
class.description: Class for Chandrayaan-1 spacecraft orientation rate parameters, roll/pitch/yaw in degrees/second since epoch

attribute.title: instrument_mode_desc
attribute.description: The instrument_mode_desc element describes the instrument mode that is identified by the instrument_mode_id element.

attribute.title: instrument_mode_id
attribute.description: The instrument_mode_id element provides an instrument-dependent designation of operating mode. This may be simply a number, letter, code, or a word.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: The mission_phase_name element provides the commonly-used identifier of a mission phase.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value was used by the mini-RF data providers for all of their archived observational data. Presumably, data from a hypothetical Chandrayaan-1 extended mission, beyond its nominal design life of 2 years, might have been distinguished by other values of this attribute. As it did not survive to the end of this period, other values proved unnecessary.

This value was used by the M3 data providers for all of their archived observational data. Presumably, data from a hypothetical Chandrayaan-1 extended mission, beyond its nominal design life of 2 years, might have been distinguished by other values of this attribute. As it did not survive to the end of this period, other values proved unnecessary.

attribute.title: orbit_limb_direction
attribute.description: The orbit_limb attribute provides the direction of the spacecraft orbit with respect to the lunar limb. valids: "Ascending", "Descending"

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Direction of the spacecraft orbit is ascending with respect to the lunar limb.
Direction of the spacecraft orbit is descending with respect to the lunar limb.

attribute.title: orbit_number
attribute.description: The orbit_number element identifies the number of the orbital revolution of the spacecraft around a target body.

attribute.title: orientation_epoch_time
attribute.description: orientation_epoch_time indicates time for the recorded orentiation.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: producer_full_name
attribute.description: The producer_full_name element provides the full_name of the individual mainly responsible for the production of a data set.

attribute.title: producer_institution_name
attribute.description: The producer_institution_name element identifies a university, research center, NASA center or other institution associated with the production of a data set. This would generally be an institution associated with the element producer_full_name.

attribute.title: release_id
attribute.description: Release_id is the identifier of a scheduled release of data by PDS. The first data release is Release 0001. The release_id for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of a time period of interest.

attribute.title: spacecraft_rotation_rate
attribute.description: Scalar rotation rate in degrees/second since epoch.

attribute.title: spacecraft_yaw_direction
attribute.description: The spacecraft_yaw_direction attribute provides the spacecraft yaw (look) mode. valids: "Forward", "Reverse"

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Defines a forward spacecraft yaw (look) mode.
Defines a reverse spacecraft yaw (look) mode.

attribute.description: Rotation about the Y-axis.

attribute.description: Rotation about the X-axis.
